She's the greatest mom to her children, the coolest grandma to her grandchildren and of course the most loving great-grandma to her grandchildren. One day she told me a stories about how the Japanese treat Indonesian at the colonial era. She was a waitress at some bar where the Japanese used to go to after they finish working. The Japanese treated her rudely as she recalls. She told me one day she saw some Indonesian making some troubles for the Japanese and the Japanese caught them and put them into the pig's cage and drown them. She was mortified about how they treated other. 
But in the end of her story, she never tells me about how she hate the Japanese, instead she had a very good relation with the Japanese.
